High performing teams can often maintain their shared mental models such that the MMOP is stable at an acceptable level as activities proceed, while the MMOP  measure of the shared mental models of a low-performing teams can fluctuate or decrease notably over time. 
A shared mental model can thus be measured in terms of the closeness of individuals" measure of the group"s MMOP to the objective measure.
This  notion can be used to measure the tightness of an emerging subgroup or guide the process of team coalition.
